{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1802,"text":"Today I want to confess something to you,"},{"time":5150,"text":"but first of all I'm going to ask you\na couple of questions."},{"time":8069,"text":"How many people here have children?"},{"time":11676,"text":"And how many of you are confident"},{"time":13278,"text":"that you know how\nto bring up your children"},{"time":15356,"text":"in exactly the right way?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":16615,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20080,"text":"OK, I don't see too many hands\ngoing up on that second one,"},{"time":23243,"text":"and that's my confession, too."},{"time":24814,"text":"I've got three boys;"},{"time":26089,"text":"they're three, nine and 12."},{"time":27920,"text":"And like you, and like most parents,"},{"time":30010,"text":"the honest truth is I have\npretty much no idea what I'm doing."},{"time":33649,"text":"I want them to be\nhappy and healthy in their lives,"},{"time":36078,"text":"but I don't know what I'm supposed to do"},{"time":38088,"text":"to make sure they are happy and healthy."},{"time":40118,"text":"There's so many books\noffering all kinds of conflicting advice,"},{"time":43119,"text":"it can be really overwhelming."},{"time":44679,"text":"So I've spent most of their lives\njust making it up as I go along."},{"time":49034,"text":"However, something changed me\na few years ago,"},{"time":52074,"text":"when I came across a little secret\nthat we have in Britain."},{"time":55365,"text":"It's helped me become more confident\nabout how I bring up my own children,"},{"time":58870,"text":"and it's revealed a lot about\nhow we as a society can help all children."},{"time":62804,"text":"I want to share that secret\nwith you today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66128,"text":"For the last 70 years,"},{"time":68089,"text":"scientists in Britain have been following\nthousands of children through their lives"},{"time":72590,"text":"as part of an incredible scientific study."},{"time":75471,"text":"There's nothing quite like it\nanywhere else in the world."},{"time":78912,"text":"Collecting information\non thousands of children"},{"time":81128,"text":"is a really powerful thing to do,"},{"time":82725,"text":"because it means we can compare\nthe ones who say,"},{"time":85036,"text":"do well at school or end up healthy\nor happy or wealthy as adults,"},{"time":88470,"text":"and the ones who struggle much more,"},{"time":90282,"text":"and then we can sift through\nall the information we've collected"},{"time":93307,"text":"and try to work out why\ntheir lives turned out different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96231,"text":"This British study --\nit's actually a kind of crazy story."},{"time":99211,"text":"So it all starts back in 1946,"},{"time":101640,"text":"just a few months\nafter the end of the war,"},{"time":103905,"text":"when scientists wanted to know"},{"time":105360,"text":"what it was like for a woman\nto have a baby at the time."},{"time":108752,"text":"They carried out\nthis huge survey of mothers"},{"time":111183,"text":"and ended up recording the birth\nof nearly every baby"},{"time":114152,"text":"born in England, Scotland\nand Wales in one week."},{"time":117127,"text":"That was nearly 14,000 babies."},{"time":120504,"text":"The questions they asked these women"},{"time":122291,"text":"are very different than the ones\nwe might ask today."},{"time":124777,"text":"They sound really old-fashioned now."},{"time":126527,"text":"They asked them things like,"},{"time":127886,"text":"\"During pregnancy,"},{"time":129116,"text":"did you get your full extra ration\nof a pint of milk a day?\""},{"time":133456,"text":"\"How much did you spend\non smocks, corsets,"},{"time":136798,"text":"nightdresses, knickers and brassieres?\""},{"time":140838,"text":"And this is my favorite one:"},{"time":142429,"text":"\"Who looked after your husband\nwhile you were in bed with this baby?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":145705,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":150248,"text":"Now, this wartime study\nactually ended up being so successful"},{"time":153667,"text":"that scientists did it again."},{"time":155460,"text":"They recorded the births\nof thousands of babies born in 1958"},{"time":158823,"text":"and thousands more in 1970."},{"time":161096,"text":"They did it again in the early 1990s,"},{"time":163122,"text":"and again at the turn of the millennium."},{"time":165194,"text":"Altogether, more than 70,000 children\nhave been involved in these studies"},{"time":168884,"text":"across those five generations."},{"time":170921,"text":"They're called the British birth cohorts,"},{"time":173136,"text":"and scientists have gone back\nand recorded more information"},{"time":175923,"text":"on all of these people\nevery few years ever since."},{"time":179091,"text":"The amount of information\nthat's now been collected on these people"},{"time":182291,"text":"is just completely mind-boggling."},{"time":183895,"text":"It includes thousands\nof paper questionnaires"},{"time":186109,"text":"and terabytes' worth of computer data."},{"time":188473,"text":"Scientists have also built up\na huge bank of tissue samples,"},{"time":191323,"text":"which includes locks of hair,\nnail clippings, baby teeth and DNA."},{"time":196498,"text":"They've even collected 9,000 placentas\nfrom some of the births,"},{"time":201077,"text":"which are now pickled in plastic buckets\nin a secure storage warehouse."},{"time":206564,"text":"This whole project has become unique --"},{"time":208484,"text":"so, no other country in the world\nis tracking generations of children"},{"time":211844,"text":"in quite this detail."},{"time":213769,"text":"These are some of the best-studied\npeople on the planet,"},{"time":216824,"text":"and the data has become\nincredibly valuable for scientists,"},{"time":219952,"text":"generating well over 6,000\nacademic papers and books."},{"time":224705,"text":"But today I want to focus\non just one finding --"},{"time":227588,"text":"perhaps the most important discovery\nto come from this remarkable study."},{"time":231946,"text":"And it's also the one\nthat spoke to me personally,"},{"time":234308,"text":"because it's about how to use science\nto do the best for our children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238588,"text":"So, let's get the bad news\nout of the way first."},{"time":242206,"text":"Perhaps the biggest message\nfrom this remarkable study is this:"},{"time":246137,"text":"don't be born into poverty\nor into disadvantage,"},{"time":249376,"text":"because if you are,"},{"time":250614,"text":"you're far more likely\nto walk a difficult path in life."},{"time":254103,"text":"Many children in this study\nwere born into poor families"},{"time":257009,"text":"or into working-class families that had\ncramped homes or other problems,"},{"time":261360,"text":"and it's clear now\nthat those disadvantaged children"},{"time":263862,"text":"have been more likely to struggle\non almost every score."},{"time":266978,"text":"They've been more likely\nto do worse at school,"},{"time":269352,"text":"to end up with worse jobs\nand to earn less money."},{"time":272131,"text":"Now, maybe that sounds really obvious,"},{"time":274162,"text":"but some of the results\nhave been really surprising,"},{"time":276881,"text":"so children who had a tough start in life"},{"time":278858,"text":"are also more likely to end up\nunhealthy as adults."},{"time":281725,"text":"They're more likely to be overweight,"},{"time":283516,"text":"to have high blood pressure,"},{"time":284875,"text":"and then decades down the line,"},{"time":286992,"text":"more likely to have a failing memory,\npoor health and even to die earlier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293777,"text":"Now, I talked about what happens later,"},{"time":296714,"text":"but some of these differences emerge\nat a really shockingly early age."},{"time":300401,"text":"In one study,"},{"time":301713,"text":"children who were growing up in poverty"},{"time":303632,"text":"were almost a year behind\nthe richer children on educational tests,"},{"time":307517,"text":"and that was by the age of just three."},{"time":310499,"text":"These types of differences have been found\nagain and again across the generations."},{"time":314381,"text":"It means that our early circumstances\nhave a profound influence"},{"time":317675,"text":"on the way that the rest\nof our lives play out."},{"time":320344,"text":"And working out why that is"},{"time":321798,"text":"is one of the most difficult questions\nthat we face today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325833,"text":"So there we have it."},{"time":327514,"text":"The first lesson for successful life,\neveryone, is this:"},{"time":330214,"text":"choose your parents very carefully."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332094,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":333119,"text":"Don't be born into a poor family\nor into a struggling family."},{"time":337369,"text":"Now, I'm sure you can see\nthe small problem here."},{"time":340130,"text":"We can't choose our parents\nor how much they earn,"},{"time":343592,"text":"but this British study has also struck\na real note of optimism"},{"time":346845,"text":"by showing that not everyone\nwho has a disadvantaged start"},{"time":350220,"text":"ends up in difficult circumstances."},{"time":353346,"text":"As you know, many people\nhave a tough start in life,"},{"time":355823,"text":"but they end up doing very well\non some measure nevertheless,"},{"time":358706,"text":"and this study starts to explain how."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361337,"text":"So the second lesson is this:"},{"time":363462,"text":"parents really matter."},{"time":365907,"text":"In this study,"},{"time":367082,"text":"children who had engaged,\ninterested parents,"},{"time":369224,"text":"ones who had ambition for their future,"},{"time":371312,"text":"were more likely to escape\nfrom a difficult start."},{"time":374170,"text":"It seems that parents and what they do\nare really, really important,"},{"time":378219,"text":"especially in the first few years of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380927,"text":"Let me give you an example of that."},{"time":382619,"text":"In one study,"},{"time":383837,"text":"scientists looked at about 17,000 children\nwho were born in 1970."},{"time":388779,"text":"They sifted all the mountains of data\nthat they had collected"},{"time":391750,"text":"to try to work out"},{"time":393001,"text":"what allowed the children\nwho'd had a difficult start in life"},{"time":395906,"text":"to go on and do well\nat school nevertheless."},{"time":398053,"text":"In other words, which ones beat the odds."},{"time":400430,"text":"The data showed that what mattered\nmore than anything else was parents."},{"time":404201,"text":"Having engaged, interested parents\nin those first few years of life"},{"time":407823,"text":"was strongly linked to children going on\nto do well at school later on."},{"time":412238,"text":"In fact, quite small things\nthat parents do"},{"time":415228,"text":"are associated with good\noutcomes for children."},{"time":418370,"text":"Talking and listening to a child,"},{"time":420299,"text":"responding to them warmly,"},{"time":422227,"text":"teaching them their letters and numbers,"},{"time":424219,"text":"taking them on trips and visits."},{"time":425915,"text":"Reading to children every day\nseems to be really important, too."},{"time":429504,"text":"So in one study,"},{"time":430916,"text":"children whose parents were reading\nto them daily when they were five"},{"time":434227,"text":"and then showing an interest\nin their education at the age of 10,"},{"time":437300,"text":"were significantly less likely\nto be in poverty at the age of 30"},{"time":441345,"text":"than those whose parents\nweren't doing those things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445111,"text":"Now, there are huge challenges\nwith interpreting this type of science."},{"time":449681,"text":"These studies show\nthat certain things that parents do"},{"time":452360,"text":"are correlated with good\noutcomes for children,"},{"time":454746,"text":"but we don't necessarily know\nthose behaviors caused the good outcomes,"},{"time":458183,"text":"or whether some other factor\nis getting in the way."},{"time":460589,"text":"For example, we have to take\ngenes into account,"},{"time":462858,"text":"and that's a whole other talk in itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465489,"text":"But scientists working\nwith this British study"},{"time":467736,"text":"are working really hard to get at causes,"},{"time":469926,"text":"and this is one study I particularly love."},{"time":471971,"text":"In this one,"},{"time":473177,"text":"they looked at the bedtime routines\nof about 10,000 children"},{"time":476068,"text":"born at the turn of the millennium."},{"time":477884,"text":"Were the children going to bed\nat regular times,"},{"time":480237,"text":"or did they go to bed\nat different times during the week?"},{"time":483159,"text":"The data showed that those children\nwho were going to bed at different times"},{"time":486756,"text":"were more likely\nto have behavioral problems,"},{"time":489153,"text":"and then those that switched\nto having regular bedtimes"},{"time":491886,"text":"often showed an improvement in behavior,"},{"time":494296,"text":"and that was really crucial,"},{"time":495676,"text":"because it suggested\nit was the bedtime routines"},{"time":497972,"text":"that were really helping things\nget better for those kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501261,"text":"Here's another one to think about."},{"time":502906,"text":"In this one,"},{"time":504088,"text":"scientists looked at children\nwho were reading for pleasure."},{"time":507003,"text":"That means that they picked up\na magazine, a picture book, a story book."},{"time":511806,"text":"The data showed that children\nwho were reading for pleasure"},{"time":514603,"text":"at the ages of five and 10"},{"time":516887,"text":"were more likely to go on in school\nbetter, on average,"},{"time":519807,"text":"on school tests later in their lives."},{"time":521802,"text":"And not just tests of reading,"},{"time":523531,"text":"but tests of spelling and maths as well."},{"time":526505,"text":"This study tried to control\nfor all the confounding factors,"},{"time":529339,"text":"so it looked at children\nwho were equally intelligent"},{"time":531847,"text":"and from the same social-class background,"},{"time":533903,"text":"so it seemed as if it was the reading\nwhich really helped those children"},{"time":537310,"text":"go on and score better on those\nschool tests later in their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541777,"text":"Now at the start,"},{"time":542951,"text":"I said the first lesson from this study"},{"time":544924,"text":"was not to be born into poverty\nor into disadvantage,"},{"time":547496,"text":"because those children tend to follow\nmore difficult paths in their lives."},{"time":551072,"text":"But then I said that parenting matters,"},{"time":553333,"text":"and that good parenting,\nif you can call it that,"},{"time":555659,"text":"helps children beat the odds"},{"time":557019,"text":"and overcome some\nof those early disadvantages."},{"time":559846,"text":"So wait,"},{"time":561195,"text":"does that actually mean, then,\nthat poverty doesn't matter after all?"},{"time":566216,"text":"You could argue it doesn't matter\nif a child is born poor --"},{"time":569252,"text":"as long as their parents are good parents,\nthey're going to do just fine."},{"time":572997,"text":"I don't believe that's true."},{"time":574428,"text":"This study shows that poverty\nand parenting matter."},{"time":577438,"text":"And one study actually\nput figures on that,"},{"time":579462,"text":"so it looked at children\ngrowing up in persistent poverty"},{"time":582185,"text":"and how well they were doing at school."},{"time":584596,"text":"The data showed"},{"time":585771,"text":"that even when their parents\nwere doing everything right --"},{"time":588651,"text":"putting them to bed on time"},{"time":589977,"text":"and reading to them every day\nand everything else --"},{"time":592438,"text":"that only got those children so far."},{"time":594610,"text":"Good parenting only reduced\nthe educational gap"},{"time":597603,"text":"between the rich and poor children\nby about 50 percent."},{"time":601472,"text":"Now that means that poverty\nleaves a really lasting scar,"},{"time":605647,"text":"and it means that if we really want\nto ensure the success and well-being"},{"time":609053,"text":"of the next generation,"},{"time":610514,"text":"then tackling child poverty\nis an incredibly important thing to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615882,"text":"Now, what does all this mean\nfor you and me?"},{"time":618294,"text":"Are there lessons here\nwe can all take home and use?"},{"time":620748,"text":"As a scientist and a journalist,"},{"time":622302,"text":"I like to have some science\nto inform my parenting ..."},{"time":625912,"text":"and I can tell you that when\nyou're shouting at your kids"},{"time":628693,"text":"to go to bed on time,"},{"time":629977,"text":"it really helps to have\nthe scientific literature on your side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633033,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":634076,"text":"And wouldn't it be great to think"},{"time":635703,"text":"that all we had to do to have\nhappy, successful children"},{"time":638436,"text":"was to talk to them,\nbe interested in their future,"},{"time":641159,"text":"put them to bed on time,\nand give them a book to read?"},{"time":643757,"text":"Our job would be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645369,"text":"Now, as you can imagine,"},{"time":646862,"text":"the answers aren't quite\nas simple as that."},{"time":650095,"text":"For one thing, this study\nlooks at what happens"},{"time":652310,"text":"to thousands and thousands\nof children on average,"},{"time":654755,"text":"but that doesn't necessarily say\nwhat will help my child or your child"},{"time":658377,"text":"or any individual child."},{"time":660138,"text":"In the end, each of our children\nis going to walk their own path,"},{"time":663370,"text":"and that's partly defined\nby the genes they inherit"},{"time":665973,"text":"and of course all the experiences\nthey have through their lives,"},{"time":668998,"text":"including their interactions\nwith us, their parents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671474,"text":"I will tell you what I did\nafter I learned all this."},{"time":673953,"text":"It's a bit embarrassing."},{"time":675952,"text":"I realized I was so busy working,"},{"time":678449,"text":"and ironically,"},{"time":679632,"text":"learning and writing about this incredible\nstudy of British children,"},{"time":683240,"text":"that there were days when I hardly\neven spoke to my own British children."},{"time":687446,"text":"So at home, we introduced talking time,"},{"time":689724,"text":"which is just 15 minutes\nat the end of the day"},{"time":691892,"text":"when we talk and listen to the boys."},{"time":694707,"text":"I try better now to ask them\nwhat they did today,"},{"time":698042,"text":"and to show that I value\nwhat they do at school."},{"time":700985,"text":"Of course, I make sure\nthey always have a book to read."},{"time":703651,"text":"I tell them I'm ambitious\nfor their future,"},{"time":705920,"text":"and I think they can be happy\nand do great things."},{"time":710009,"text":"I don't know that any of that\nwill make a difference,"},{"time":712815,"text":"but I'm pretty confident\nit won't do them any harm,"},{"time":715229,"text":"and it might even do them some good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717735,"text":"Ultimately, if we want happy children,"},{"time":720603,"text":"all we can do is listen to the science,"},{"time":722667,"text":"and of course,"},{"time":723857,"text":"listen to our children themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725707,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}